iology of world religions and by exploring intercivilizational encounters in key world regions. The essays within this volume are of unusual interest for their original analysis of relatively neglected civilizational zones, especially Islam and the Islamicate civilization and the Byzantine civilization, and its continuation in Orthodox Russia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilizationxPhilosophy. 0aReligion and civilization. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Cultural Anthropology. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aHistory : World History. 4aSociology : Sociology of Religion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh1 aArjomand, Saïd Amir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArjomand, Saïd Amir, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHalton, Eugene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalberg, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalberg, Stephen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLidz, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMotta, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNielsen, Donald A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProzorova, Yulia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalvatore, Armando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWittrock, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848341240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438483412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438483412/origi